Package fu.esi

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ESI
    This class models the Extended Split Index (ESI) as desribed in Jörg Roth: The Extended Split Index to Efficiently Store and Retrieve Spatial Data With Standard Databases IADIS International Conference Applied Computing 2009, Rom (Italien), 19.-21.
    ESIentry
    An ESI intex entry.
    IMI_ESI<T>
    Encapsulates an Extended Split Index that fully resides in memory (IMI, In-Memory-Index).
    IMI_ESI_ByteArray
    Encapsulates an Extended Split Index that fully resides in memory (IMI, In-Memory-Index).
    IMI_ESI_Int
    Encapsulates an Extended Split Index that fully resides in memory (IMI, In-Memory-Index).
    IMI_NearIndex<T>
    A NearIndex allows to query for the nearest object to a certain point.
    IMI_NearIndex_ByteArray
    A NearIndex allows to query for the nearest object to a certain point.
    IMI_NearIndex_Int
    A NearIndex allows to query for the nearest object to a certain point.
    SQL
    This class helps to generate SQL code that considers index colums without the need to use JAXME_SQL
